-- 2012-03-19T21:05:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-19/peru-stocks-candente-irl-maple-relapasa-rio-alto.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 3:10 p.m. local time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose for the first session in four,
gaining 0.5 percent to 23,079.77. The  MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD) 
gained 0.3 percent to 2,893.05.  Refineria la Pampilla SA  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Repsol
YPF SA, climbed 2.8 percent to 1.09 soles after crude gained in
New York, said Hernando Pastor, an analyst at Lima-based Kallpa
Securities SAB.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, advanced 1.6 percent to $1.29.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian copper
exploration company, jumped 4.8 percent to $1.10 after copper
rebounded in New York.  Southern Copper Corp. (PCU\C)  (SCCO PE), Peruâ€™s biggest copper
producer, rose 1.1 percent to $32.33.  Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POM\C)  (POMALCC1 PE), a sugar
producer, gained 3.6 percent to 58 centimos after sugar advanced
earlier in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
